The [[Talz/Legends|Talz]] [[Thief/Legends|thief]] [[Muftak/Legends|Muftak]] released an autobiographical [[Book/Legends|novel]] entitled '''''Sands in Winter'''''. Despite being regarded as simple on his<ref name="FF93" /> [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]]<ref name="EGC">''[[The Essential Guide to Characters]]''</ref> of [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], the Talz developed enough eloquence to tell his story<ref name="FF93" /> about how his larval sack was accidentally loaded onto an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Freighter/Legends|freighter]] going to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]].<ref name="EGAS">[[The Essential Guide to Alien Species (real-world book)|''The Essential Guide to Alien Species'']]</ref> The book became a best seller and ensured that Muftak and his<ref name="FF93">{{FactFile|93|CAN 19-20|Mos Eisley Cantina Characters}}</ref> adopted [[Chadra-Fan/Legends|Chadra-Fan]] [[Gender/Legends|daughter]]<ref name="Kabe-GF">{{Topps|set=2013 Topps Star Wars Galactic Files Series 2|cardname=Kabe (Cantina Patron)|link=https://www.tcdb.com/ViewCard.cfm/sid/93283/cid/6569390/2013-Topps-Star-Wars:-Galactic-Files-Series-2-365-Kabe|archivedate=20231120031347}}</ref> [[Kabe/Legends|Kabe]] would never have to worry about [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] again.<ref name="FF93" />

==Behind the scenes==
''Sands in Winter'' was first mentioned in the [[2001]] reference book ''[[The Essential Guide to Alien Species (real-world book)|The Essential Guide to Alien Species]]'', written by [[Ann Margaret Lewis (real person)|Ann Margaret Lewis]].<ref name="EGAS" />

